gameRecap.title: Game Recap: Jazz 124, Thunder 117
gameRecap.excerpt: The Jazz outscore the Thunder 63-49 in the 2nd half to defeat the Thunder, 124-117. For Utah, Lauri Markkanen led the way with 33 points (5-7 3PT FG) and 11 rebounds with John Collins adding 22 points and nine rebounds. Shai Gilgeous-Alexander led the way with 28 points, seven assists, and four rebounds aided by Jalen Williams tallying 26 points (three 3PM), five rebounds, and five assists and Chet Holmgren putting up 22 points (four 3PM), eight rebounds, and four blocks for Oklahoma City in the losing effort. Utah wins and improves to 26-26 on the season, while Oklahoma City moves to 35-16 with the loss.
